  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Prepare the cure by mixing palm sugar, cure, salt, and black pepper in a small bowl.",
    "Season cod fillets with the cure mixture and place them on a plate.",
    "Let it sit for 10 minutes and then rinse under cold water.",
    "Dry the cod fillets using paper towels.",
    "Heat olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add dried rose petals and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add cod fillets, lemon juice, and water to the Dutch oven.",
    "Cover the pot and transfer it to the preheated oven.",
    "Bake for 12 minutes or until the fish is cooked through.",
    "Garnish with fresh parsley and fresh mint.",
    "Serve hot."
